(36, 'document', 'text/html', 'Terms and Conditions', 'Terms and Conditions', 'Terms and Conditions', 'terms-and-conditions', 'Terms and Conditions', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '<h2 class="dec">The Wedding Website Group Terms and Conditions</h2>\r\n<p>This\r\n"Agreement" is a contract between each party ("User") who\r\naccesses TheWeddingWebsiteGroup.com site (the "Site") and the\r\nproprietor of the Site ("24 Seven Communications", a company having a\r\nplace of business in Leeds, UK) regarding access to, and use of, the Site. </p>\r\n<p>By\r\naccessing, or otherwise using, the Site, User agrees to be bound by this\r\nAgreement and acknowledges the consideration provided by The Wedding Website\r\nGroup in support of this Agreement, and particularly including the disclaimers,\r\nlimitation of liability and provisions related to prohibited conduct and\r\nremedies set-out herein.</p>\r\n<p>The\r\nWedding Website Group reserves the right to change this Agreement at its sole\r\ndiscretion by posting revisions on the Site. Continued accessing, or otherwise\r\nusing, the Site following any such revision(s) constitutes acceptance of the\r\nrevised Agreement.</p>\r\n<p>USER\r\nAGREES TO REVIEW THIS AGREEMENT AND ANY CHANGES THERETO REGULARLY ENOUGH DURING\r\nTHE PERIOD OF TIME IN WHICH SUCH USER ACCESSES THE SITE TO ENSURE THAT SUCH\r\nUSER REMAINS FAMILIAR AND IN COMPLIANCE WITH THIS AGREEMENT. Any User not\r\nagreeing with this Agreement or any changes to or revisions thereof must\r\nterminate access to, or other use of, the Site immediately.</p>\r\n<p><strong>1. Registration, Accounts and Passwords.</strong></p>\r\n<p>The\r\nWedding Website Group site includes a number of wedding related services\r\n("Services") such as personalisation, web hosting, and others helpful\r\ntools such as direction services, all made available after registration. A User\r\nagrees to provide accurate and current information for such registration, and\r\nto update such information completely and timel